"Paladin: Paladin Subclass":
  title: "Paladin: Paladin Subclass (3rd Level)"
  desc: "You gain the Oath of Devotion subclass or another Paladin subclass of your choice. The Oath of Devotion is detailed after the Paladin's class description, and other subclasses will appear in future Unearthed Arcana articles.\n\nA subclass is a specialization that grants you special abilities at certain Paladin levels. For the rest of your career, you gain each of your subclass's features that are of your Paladin level and lower. This class's description tells you the levels when your subclass provides features."
  fields:
  - body: "[One D&D Packet 4: Druid & Paladin](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/one-dnd/druid-paladin)"

"Paladin: Feat":
  title: "Paladin: Feat (4th, 8th, 12th, 16th and 19th Level)"
  desc: "You gain the Ability Score Improvement Feat or another Feat of your choice for which you qualify."
  fields:
  - body: "[One D&D Packet 4: Druid & Paladin](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/one-dnd/druid-paladin)"

"Paladin: Extra Attack":
  title: "Paladin: Extra Attack (5th Level)"
  desc: "You can attack twice, instead of once, whenever you take the Attack action on your turn."
  fields:
  - body: "[One D&D Packet 4: Druid & Paladin](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/one-dnd/druid-paladin)"

"Paladin: Faithful Steed":
  title: "Paladin: Faithful Steed (5th Level)"
  desc: "You can easily call on the aid of an otherworldly steed. You always have the Find Steed spell prepared, and it doesn't count against the number of spells you can prepare.\n\nWhen you cast this spell, its casting time is an action. You can also cast the spell once without expending a Spell Slot, and you regain the ability to do so when you finish a Long Rest."
  fields:
  - body: "[One D&D Packet 4: Druid & Paladin](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/one-dnd/druid-paladin)"

"Paladin: Aura of Protection":
  title: "Paladin: Aura of Protection (7th Level)"
  desc: "You radiate a protective, invisible aura that extends 10 feet from you in every direction, but it doesn't extend through Total Cover.\n\nYou and your allies in the aura gain a bonus to saving throws equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum bonus of +1).\n\nIf another Paladin is present, a creature can benefit from only one Aura of Protection at a time; the creature chooses which one when entering the auras."
  fields:
  - body: "[One D&D Packet 4: Druid & Paladin](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/one-dnd/druid-paladin)"

"Paladin: Abjure Foes":
  title: "Paladin: Abjure Foes (9th Level)"
  desc: "As a Magic action, you can expend one use of your Channel Divinity to overwhelm foes with divine awe. As you present your Holy Symbol or weapon, you can target a number of creatures equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum of one creature) that you can see within 60 feet of yourself.\n\nEach target must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the target has the Dazed and Frightened conditions for 1 minute or until it takes any damage. On a successful save, the target has the Dazed condition for 1 minute or until it takes any damage."
  fields:
  - body: "[One D&D Packet 4: Druid & Paladin](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/one-dnd/druid-paladin)"

"Paladin: Radiant Strikes":
  title: "Paladin: Radiant Strikes (11th Level)"
  desc: "You are so suffused with divine might that your weapon strikes carry supernatural power with them. When you hit a target with an attack roll using a Simple or Martial weapon, the target takes an extra 1d8 Radiant damage."
  fields:
  - body: "[One D&D Packet 4: Druid & Paladin](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/one-dnd/druid-paladin)"

"Paladin: Aura of Courage":
  title: "Paladin: Aura of Courage (13th Level)"
  desc: "You and your allies are immune to the Frightened condition while in your Aura of Protection. If a Frightened ally enters the aura, that condition is suppressed while the ally is there."
  fields:
  - body: "[One D&D Packet 4: Druid & Paladin](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/one-dnd/druid-paladin)"

"Paladin: Restoring Touch":
  title: "Paladin: Restoring Touch (15th Level)"
  desc: "When you use Lay on Hands on a creature, you can also remove one or more of the following conditions from the creature: Blinded, Charmed, Dazed, Deafened, Frightened, Paralyzed, or Stunned. You must expend 5 Hit Points from the healing pool of Lay on Hands for each of these conditions you remove; those points don't also restore Hit Points to the creature."
  fields:
  - body: "[One D&D Packet 4: Druid & Paladin](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/one-dnd/druid-paladin)"

"Paladin: Aura Expansion":
  title: "Paladin: Aura Expansion (17th Level)"
  desc: "Your Aura of Protection now extends 30 feet from you rather than 10 feet."
  fields:
  - body: "[One D&D Packet 4: Druid & Paladin](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/one-dnd/druid-paladin)"

"Paladin: Divine Conduit":
  title: "Paladin: Divine Conduit (18th Level)"
  desc: "Whenever you roll Initiative, you regain one use of this class's Channel Divinity."
  fields:
  - body: "[One D&D Packet 4: Druid & Paladin](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/one-dnd/druid-paladin)"

"Paladin: Epic Boon":
  title: "Paladin: Epic Boon (20th Level)"
  desc: "You gain the following benefits:\n\n**Ability Score Increase**. Choose one of your ability scores. That score increases by 2, and this increase can raise the score above 20 but not above 30.\n\n**Epic Boon Feat**. You gain the Epic Boon of Truesight or another Epic Boon feat of your choice."
  fields:
  - body: "[One D&D Packet 4: Druid & Paladin](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/one-dnd/druid-paladin)"


