# PALADIN: OATH OF DEVOTION FEATURES
# ===================================

"Oath of Devotion: Oath Spells":
  title: "Oath of Devotion: Oath Spells (3rd Level)"
  desc: "The magic of your oath gives you the following benefits:\n\n**Prepared Spells**. You always have certain spells ready; when you reach a Paladin level specified in the Oath of Devotion Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared. These spells don't count against the number of spells you can prepare, and they follow the rules of this class's Spellcasting feature.\n\n**Free Casting**. You can cast one of your prepared spells from this feature without expending a Spell Slot, and you must finish a Long Rest before you use this benefit again."
  fields:
  - title: Oath of Devotion Spells
    body: "```\n| Paladin Level | Spells\n|---------------+--------\n| 3rd           | Protection from Evil And Good, Shield of Faith\n| 5th           | Aid, Zone of Truth\n| 9th           | Aura of Vitality, Blinding Smite\n| 13th          | Guardian of Faith, Staggering Smite\n| 17th          | Commune, Flame Strike\n```"
  - body: "[One D&D Packet 4: Druid & Paladin](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/one-dnd/druid-paladin)"

"Oath of Devotion: Sacred Weapon":
  title: "Oath of Devotion: Sacred Weapon (3rd Level)"
  desc: "As a Bonus Action, you can expend one use of your Channel Divinity to imbue one Simple or Martial weapon that you are holding with positive energy. For 1 minute, you add your Charisma modifier to attack rolls you make with that weapon (minimum bonus of +1), and each time you hit with it, you cause it to deal its normal damage type or Radiant damage.\n\nThe weapon also emits bright light in a 20-foot radius and dim light 20 feet beyond that.\n\nYou can end this effect as a Bonus Action. This effect also ends if you aren't holding or carrying the weapon or if you have the Incapacitated condition."
  fields:
  - body: "[One D&D Packet 4: Druid & Paladin](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/one-dnd/druid-paladin)"

"Oath of Devotion: Smite of Protection":
  title: "Oath of Devotion: Smite of Protection (6th Level)"
  desc: "Your Divine Smite now radiates protective energy that allows you and your allies to stay in the fight. Whenever you use your Divine Smite, choose yourself or an ally within 30 feet of yourself. The chosen creature gains Temporary Hit Points equal to 1d8 plus the level of the Spell Slot used for the Divine Smite."
  fields:
  - body: "[One D&D Packet 4: Druid & Paladin](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/one-dnd/druid-paladin)"

"Oath of Devotion: Aura of Devotion":
  title: "Oath of Devotion: Aura of Devotion (10th Level)"
  desc: "You and your allies are immune to the Charmed condition while in your Aura of Protection. If a Charmed ally enters the aura, that condition is suppressed while the ally is there."
  fields:
  - body: "[One D&D Packet 4: Druid & Paladin](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/one-dnd/druid-paladin)"

"Oath of Devotion: Holy Nimbus":
  title: "Oath of Devotion: Holy Nimbus (14th Level)"
  desc: "As a Bonus Action, you can imbue your Aura of Protection with holy power. The aura gains the following benefits for 1 minute or until you end them as a Bonus Action:\n\n**Radiant Damage**. Whenever an enemy starts its turn in the aura, that creature takes Radiant damage equal to your Proficiency Bonus plus your Charisma modifier.\n\n**Sunlight**. The aura is filled with bright light that is sunlight.\n\nOnce you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a Long Rest unless you expend a Spell Slot of at least 4th level when you use it again."
  fields:
  - body: "[One D&D Packet 4: Druid & Paladin](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/one-dnd/druid-paladin)"
